Usage: loadBoard (lb) [flags] [arg path]
Arguments: arg path - some directory with a file that conforms to the Board format.
Flags: -n
Description:
This command will by default load a Go Board file from /src/saveData/boards/board (Linux) or \src\saveData\boards\board (Windows). If provided with a path argument it will read from that path instead.
Flag Descriptions:
-n  Stands for "name" and will load a given file name from the default directory (see Description). Useful if one doesn't want to type lots of directories.